    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our offensive core is anchored by **Daulton Varsho** (72.31) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (69.99), who serve as our highest-upside plays. **Daulton Varsho** benefits from a massive 19% SP skill boost against Simeon Woods Richardson, while the veteran **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** enjoys a favorable environment against J.T. Ginn, where his ability to capitalize on a slow delivery profiles well for our target category of stolen bases. **Tyler Freeman** (69.37) also warrants attention; a significant 14% park factor boost makes him an unexpected but high-value start in his matchup against Grant Holmes. We are also leaning on **Will Smith** (61.83) and **Bryson Stott** (61.22), the latter of whom is a priority start due to a favorable platoon edge and the high likelihood of a stolen base opportunity against the slower delivery of Eury P\u00e9rez.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Cal Raleigh** (51.28), who finished just outside the starting threshold. Despite a solid projection, the optimizer faded **Cal Raleigh** due to a brutal 19% downgrade against the elite arm of Cole Ragans, favoring the higher-floor efficiency of our primary backstops. While we are keeping a close eye on **Geraldo Perdomo** (59.00), note that his aggressive projection is tempered by a 5% penalty for wind-in conditions, which could suppress his expected output. We are also proceeding with caution regarding **Luis Arraez** (49.11) and **Wenceel Perez** (49.11); both players face tough matchups\u2014**Luis Arraez** against the arm of Shane McClanahan and **Wenceel Perez** against Gore\u2014making them high-variance plays that require close monitoring of official lineups to ensure they maintain their projected slots. \n\nPlease note that virtually every roster spot currently carries a \"Lineup Pending\" tag, introducing inherent volatility into today's strategy. Should **Will Smith**, **Yainer Diaz**, or any of our infielders like **Gleyber Torres** or **Matt Chapman** drop in the batting order, their efficiency scores will adjust downward significantly. We are keeping **Jonathan Aranda**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Jeremiah Jackson** on high alert; should any late-scratch news emerge regarding our starters, these bench pieces are prepared to rotate in to preserve our game caps. We are proceeding without **Masyn Winn**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, or **Drew Gilbert** in the active lineup today, as they failed to crack the top-tier efficiency requirements against today\u2019s opposing rotation.",
